analysisPopulations.name: All Randomized Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: All Randomized Analysis Set includes all subjects who were randomized in the study.
analysisPopulations.label: All Randomized
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All Randomized Analysis Set includes all subjects who were randomized in the study.

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) includes all subjects who took at least 1 dose of study drug and were randomized into the study. This is the primary analysis set for efficacy analyses.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) includes all subjects who took at least 1 dose of study drug and were randomized into the study. This is the primary analysis set for efficacy analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >= 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Safety Analysis Set includes all subjects who took at least 1 dose of study drug. This is the primary analysis set for safety analyses.
analysisPopulations.label: Safety
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Safety Analysis Set includes all subjects who took at least 1 dose of study drug. This is the primary analysis set for safety analyses.

analysisPopulations.name: PK Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: For the PK Analysis Set, subjects will be grouped according to the actual treatment they received.
analysisPopulations.label: PK
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: For the PK Analysis Set, subjects will be grouped according to the actual treatment they received.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Subjects with evaluable PK data (implied by grouping requirements)

characteristics.name: Diabetes mellitus
characteristics.description: Presence or absence of diabetes mellitus as determined by medical history or based on the screening laboratory values (HbA1c >= 6.5% or fasting plasma glucose >= 126 mg/dL)

characteristics.name: Cirrhosis
characteristics.description: Presence or absence of cirrhosis (F4 vs. Non-F4) as determined by the central biopsy reader at screening

characteristics.name: Age
characteristics.description: Age in years on the date of the first dose of study drug
